An All Progressives Congress (APC) governorship aspirant in Bauchi State, Nura Manu Soro, has donated 20 cars and 225 motorcycles to the party in the state. Distributing the items in Bauchi, the aspirant said each local government was given one car, while the motorcycles would be distributed to the 225 political wards across the state. He said the donation was his contribution to the building of the party in the state. “I am one of the loyal and law-abiding members of the party in the state and I deem it fit to make such contribution to strengthen our party; the contribution came from my friends and well-wishers,” he said. He said the party was ready and determined to take over the state from the ruling Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in 2023. He urged the leaders of the party to continue with their effort to promote peace, unity and justice adding, “whoever wins the primary election should be supported by all members of the party to succeed.” Receiving the donation, the state chairman of the party, Babayo Aliyu Misau, thanked the aspirant, assuring that a level playing field would be provided to all aspirants during the primary election in the state.